 ### Setup
 
 - Selected agent backends now persist globally, so new projects inherit your choice instead of re-prompting each time.
+- New `hive setup` local provisioner validates the non-Docker toolchain, bootstraps Hive-owned dependencies (`qmd`, web bundle), installs the daemon with the current binary, enrolls the current project, and launches or services local web.
+- `hive web` now has a managed-service lifecycle (`install/start/stop/status`) beside the foreground run path, with systemd-user/launchd units for a separate `hive-web` service.
+- Non-loopback web binds are now refused unless GitHub owner auth is configured or the operator explicitly uses `--unsafe` / `web.allow_public_unsafe: true`.
+- `hive daemon status --json` reports binary/version consistency and the web dashboard surfaces daemon health with a guarded repair action.
 
 ### Telegram bot
 
