+## Local Web (Source Checkout Only)
+
+The released `hive-cli` gem does not package the Rails app. Do not treat a missing `web/` directory as an install failure for Homebrew, AUR, or `install.sh` installs. If the user is installing from a Hive source checkout, or has set `HIVEBOX_WEB_APP_DIR` to a checkout's `web/` directory, offer the local web flow:
+
+```bash
+"$hive_cmd" setup --json --yes
+"$hive_cmd" web status --json
+```
+
+Use `"$hive_cmd" setup --service --yes` when the user wants the separate `hive-web` user service installed and started. Otherwise `hive setup` finishes by launching the foreground web server. Local web binds to `127.0.0.1:4567` by default. Do not suggest a non-loopback bind unless GitHub owner auth is configured, or the user explicitly accepts `--unsafe` / `web.allow_public_unsafe: true`.
+
