+## Binary consistency
+
+`hive daemon status --json` compares the invoking CLI's resolved binary and
+`Hive::VERSION` with two daemon-side signals: the installed unit's
+`HIVE_BIN`/`ExecStart` path and the running daemon's PID-file metadata
+(`hive_binary`, `hive_version`) when the daemon is alive. Paths are normalized
+through realpath where possible so ruby-manager shims and symlinks do not
+produce unnecessary drift. A mismatch sets `binary_consistent: false` and
+returns `repair_command: "hive daemon install --force"`.
+
+The repair mechanism is intentionally the existing installer: `hive daemon
+install --force` rewrites the systemd-user/launchd unit from the current CLI
+binary and restarts/reloads as the platform installer already does.
+[[commands/setup]] uses this path during local provision, and [[commands/web]]
+shows the same health block plus a guarded repair action in the Rails
+dashboard.
+
