+live on the `/data` mount in hivebox), run `bin/rails db:prepare`, then exec
+`bin/rails server`. Outside the container or a source checkout the command
+exits 1 with guidance — the gem itself does not package the Rails app
+(`test/unit/gemspec_test.rb` pins that). Foreground web rejects `--json`
+because it execs a long-lived server; use `hive web status --json` for
+machine-readable health.
+
+`hive web install` writes the platform-native `hive-web` unit
+(`~/.config/systemd/user/hive-web.service` on Linux,
+`~/Library/LaunchAgents/local.hive-web.plist` on macOS), points it at the same
+resolved Hive binary as the invoking CLI, and enables/starts it when the user
+service manager is available. Without `--force`, a drifted existing unit is
+left untouched and the command exits with guidance to rerun
+`hive web install --force`; `--force` saves a timestamped backup before
+overwriting. `hive web status --json` emits `hive-web-status.v1` with
+service-installed/enabled state and an HTTP health probe against the configured
+loopback URL. `hive web install --json` emits `hive-web-install.v1`.
+
+## Local setup
+
+`hive setup` is the orchestrator for source-checkout local mode; see
+[[commands/setup]]. It runs dependency preflight, bootstraps Hive-owned deps
+(`qmd` and the web bundle), persists backend choices, installs the daemon with
+the current binary, enrolls the current registered project, and then launches
+foreground web or installs/starts `hive-web` with `--service`.
+
+## Bind safety
+
+The default config remains unauthenticated loopback:
+
+```yaml
+web:
+  bind: 127.0.0.1
+  port: 4567
+  origin: http://127.0.0.1:4567
+```
+
+Loopback binds (`127.0.0.0/8`, `::1`, `localhost`) boot normally. Non-loopback
+binds, including `0.0.0.0`, are refused unless GitHub owner auth is configured
+or the operator explicitly passes `--unsafe` / sets
+`web.allow_public_unsafe: true`. The explicit unsafe path preserves the old
+warn-and-proceed behavior for operators who put another trusted gate in front
+of the process.
 
