+## Local web packaging gap (2026-07-12)
+
+`hive setup` and `hive web` now make non-Docker local web first-class for a
+source checkout, but the `hive-cli` gem still does not package the Rails `web/`
+app. Pure gem installs therefore need Docker/hivebox for the packaged browser
+surface, or an explicit `HIVEBOX_WEB_APP_DIR` pointing at a checkout. Future
+packaging work can decide whether embedding the Rails app in the gem is worth
+the artifact size and dependency-management cost. Until then, docs should keep
+calling local web a source-checkout mode. See [[commands/setup]] and
+[[commands/web]].
